HEADWORD: Saxhorn
<hw>Sax"horn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
name given to a numerous family of brass wind instruments with valves,
invented by Antoine Joseph Adolphe <etsep>Sax</etsep> (known as Adolphe
Sax), of Belgium and Paris, and much used in military bands and in
orchestras.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saxicava</ent>⟦br⟧
